.

  
  

** Location: Brisbane, Australia **

** Fixed Term Contract until 20 September 2024, with possible extension to permanent role **

** Role Purpose: **

We are seeking a highly motivated and experienced Bot Controller to join our
team. The ideal candidate will be responsible for building, testing, and
deploying conversational AI-powered Chatbot- & Voicebots for various customer-
facing platforms such as websites, messaging apps, and Voice Channels. The Bot
Controller will work closely with cross-functional stakeholders, including
Product Managers, UX designers, and Process Excellences teams, to understand
and meet the Business needs.

** Key responsibilities include: **

  * Build and maintain Chatbot & Voicebots using no-code/low-code solutions 
  * Work with stakeholders to understand business requirements and design Chatbot & Voicebot workflows accordingly 
  * Collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure smooth integration with existing systems and data sources 
  * Stay up to date with the latest Chatbot & Voicebot technology trends and assess new solutions for potential implementation 
  * Provide technical support and troubleshoot issues related to Chatbot & Voicebots 
  * Document Chatbot & Voicebot solutions and contribute to the overall knowledge base 
  * Participate in the continuous improvement of Chatbot & Voicebot development processes 

** As the successful AI Chatbot and Voicebot Controller, you'll be able to show experience: **

Preferred:

  * Firsthand experience in building and maintaining Chatbot & Voicebots using no-code/low-code solutions 
  * Knowledge of bot workflows and NLP techniques 
  * Firsthand experience integrating Chatbot & Voicebots with existing systems and data sources 
  * Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail 
  * Good communication and collaboration skills 
  * Familiarity with Agile software development methodologies 
  * Ability to work in a fast-paced and dynamic environment 

